            <h3>Tangub City’s Must Do List</h3>
            <ol><li>1. Prepare for an exciting adventure such as Malindang trail trekking, boating, swimming and zipline. Points of interest include Hoyohoy Highland Park found at the foot of Mt. Malindang Range where one can have the panoramic view of Panguil Bay, the cities of Ozamiz and Tangub and the neighboring places of Zamboanga del Sur, Lanao del Norte, and Iligan City.
                </li><li>2. Dance with the Sinanduloy Cultural Troupe. It is an award winning cultural troupe managed by local government of Tangub
                </li><li>3. Eat luscious evergreen Tangub mangoes, tasty mudcrabs and shrimps, exotic seafood like igud, ubod, and tamban- gongo.
                </li><li>4. Buy any salted mussels/sisi at Centennial Rest Area grounds, galletas from Obut bakery at barangay Sta. Maria, souve- nir and novelty items at City Café 1 and City Café 2 and evergreen mangoes, mudcrabs, prawns, and shrimps from Agora Public Market.
                </li><li>5. Spend a worry-free vacation with the laidback character of the city
                </li></ol><h3>Tourism Profile</h3>
