                <h4>How to get there
            </h4><p>
                From Cagayan De Oro City, take the bus (Rural Transit or Super 5 Bus) from Cagayan De Oro west bound Bus Terminal bound for Dipolog or Ozamiz City. Upon reaching Mukas, La- nao Del Norte, there is a 10-15 minutes barge ride to reach Ozamiz City port, then a jeepney or bus to Tangub City.</p>
            <p>By sea, from Cebu City, an overnight boat trip to the port of Ozamiz City then a jeepney or bus bound to Tangub City. From Manila, a two-night boat trip to the port of Ozamiz City then a jeepney or bus bound for Tangub City.</p>
            <h4>For travel information
            </h4><p>Please contact the City Tourism Office at telephone nos. (088) 354-1591 or email at tangub_tourism@yahoo.com
                There are no direct flights to Tangub City. However, flights from Manila and Cebu have routes to Cagayan De Oro City, Dipolog City, Ozamiz City, and Pagadian City from where Tangub can be reached by land.</p>
            <p>From Ozamiz City, take the Rural Bus or Suscir Bus located at the Integrated Bus and Jeepney Terminal (IBJT/Agora Terminal) for a roughly 20-minute ride.</p>
            <p>From Pagadian City, take an air-conditioned, deluxe, or stationary bus of Rural Transit, or Super 5 Bus Company that is bound for either Dipolog or Ozamiz. These buses have stopovers in Tangub City.</p>
